    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-12-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1039"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1039">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Thomas</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-12-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 5, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 100.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to instruction No. 96 of October 23
                    last, I now inclose for your information a copy of a note<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d1039fn1">Printed, <ref target="#pg_476">p. 476</ref>.</note> sent
                    to the chargé d’affaires ad interim of the French Republic at this capital,
                    informing him that you have been instructed to act in concert with your German
                    and British colleagues touching the inclusion of such claims of foreigners as
                    arose in the Samoan group of islands in the arbitration to be submitted to His
                    Majesty the King of Sweden and Norway.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
